&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BMS BSW &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;oftware Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Responsible for BMS BSW development, testing and maintenance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Responsible for configuration and debugging of BMS AUTOSAR BSW&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Responsible for the BMS bootloader and complex drivers development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Responsible for BMS CAN Communication, network management and UDS diagnostic development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Responsible for BMS XCP and J1939 protocol development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Bachelor’s degree or above, major in vehicle engineering, computer, electronic and electrical, automation, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
