&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an exceptional Leader to head SES&#39;s global Materials BU, owning strategy, P&amp;amp;L, customer development, product direction, and cross-functional execution across the U.S., Asia, and EU. This role combines business development, product/market leadership, and technical fluency in next-generation battery materials, with responsibility for scaling commercial electrolyte and materials programs that support our ESS and Drone platforms. We are seeking a hands-on, first-principles operator with deep experience in the chemical, materials, or electrolyte ecosystem - preferably with strong Japan/Korea industry networks - and the ability to drive both commercial and technical outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Own all Sales and Business Development for Materials BU, including revenue, gross margin, cost structure, and annual operating plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Develop and execute a 1-3 year strategy covering markets, partners, product priorities, and capacity needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Build annual/quarterly plans with Finance, Legal, and executive leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Development &amp;amp; Customer Expansion (US/EU focus):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Lead go-to-market strategy for electrolyte and key battery materials, driving growth with enterprise OEM, Tier-1, and chemical supplier customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Expand commercial relationships across Japan and Kore

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mechanical Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsible for the analysis and evaluation of power battery cell selection, structural materials and product structure design scheme according to customer SOR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsible for the schematic design of power battery PACK battery system and modules, detailed design of 3D digital model and 2D drawings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsible for the safety and reliability design of power battery PACK battery system and module level&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Systematically analyzed the problems found in trial production, mass production and user feedback, and put forward improvement suggestions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsible for sample sending and making, processing progress tracking, sample confirmation, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsible for testing and verification of Pack system and parts, design optimization according to regulations or customer requirements, and structural improvement for mass production&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prepare design specifications and patents&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor’s degree or above, major in electrochemistry, Vehicle engineering, Mechatronics, polymer materials, Electrical engineering, automation, etc&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More than 3 years of experience in power battery PACK structure design, experience in product G&amp;amp;D drawing, dimension chain analysis, ability to independently design pack battery system structure, independent structural strength simulation ability is preferred&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in composite material structure design and structural airworthiness verification of aircraft is preferred&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Familiar with battery electrical related professional knowledge, battery selection and testing experience is preferred&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with the characteristics and application range of metal materials and plastic materials, proficient in injection molding process, sheet metal processing process, surface treatment, etc., skilled in Solidworks, CATIA, UG and other design software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Able to read and write in English&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work hard, careful and rigorous, have a sense of responsibility and good team spirit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

